---
import MainLayout from '../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
---

<MainLayout
  title="Text Case Converter — UPPERCASE, lowercase, Title Case | DevSuite"
  description="Free online text case converter. Transform text to UPPERCASE, lowercase, Title Case, Sentence case, and strip extra whitespace instantly."
  canonicalPath="/case-converter"

  toolName="Case Converter"
  toolDescription="Instantly convert text to UPPERCASE, lowercase, Title Case, or Sentence case."
>
  <div class="ad-layout">
    <aside class="ad-sidebar" aria-hidden="true">
      AdSense Unit | Responsive Vertical Skyscraper
    </aside>

    <div class="ad-workspace">
      <div class="workspace-header">
        <h1>Text Case Converter</h1>
        <p>Paste your text below, pick a transformation, and copy the result.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="workspace-section">
        <label class="input-label" for="case-input">Input Text</label>
        <textarea class="input" id="case-input" rows="8" placeholder="Paste or type your text here..."></textarea>
      </div>

      <div class="stats-bar" id="stats-bar">
        <div class="stat-item">Words: <span class="stat-value" id="stat-words">0</span></div>
        <div class="stat-item">Characters: <span class="stat-value" id="stat-chars">0</span></div>
        <div class="stat-item">Paragraphs: <span class="stat-value" id="stat-paras">0</span></div>
      </div>

      <div class="workspace-section">
        <div class="section-label">Transformations</div>
        <div class="btn-group">
          <button class="btn" id="btn-upper" type="button">UPPERCASE</button>
          <button class="btn" id="btn-lower" type="button">lowercase</button>
          <button class="btn" id="btn-title" type="button">Title Case</button>
          <button class="btn" id="btn-sentence" type="button">Sentence Case</button>
          <button class="btn" id="btn-clean" type="button">Clean Whitespace</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="workspace-section">
        <label class="input-label" for="case-output">Output</label>
        <textarea class="input" id="case-output" rows="8" readonly placeholder="Transformed text will appear here..."></textarea>
      </div>

      <div class="btn-group">
        <button class="btn btn-primary" id="btn-copy" type="button">Copy Output</button>
        <button class="btn" id="btn-clear" type="button">Clear All</button>
      </div>
    
      <!-- MASSIVE SEO PROSE SECTION -->
      <section class="prose" style="margin-top: 4rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border); padding-top: 2rem;">
        <h2>The Ultimate Text Case Converter Tool</h2>
        <p>Whether you need to fix a document typed entirely in caps lock, format headlines for your blog, or clean up messy user input, our <strong>free online text case converter</strong> is the perfect tool for the job. Instead of manually retyping paragraphs of text, you can instantly transform any string into UPPERCASE, lowercase, Title Case, or Sentence case with a single click. This <strong>online capitalization tool</strong> is designed for writers, editors, developers, and data entry professionals who need to standardize text formats quickly.</p>
        
        <h3>Why Use a Case Converter?</h3>
        <p>Text formatting inconsistencies are incredibly common, especially when compiling data from multiple sources or dealing with legacy systems. A reliable <strong>letter case converter</strong> saves hours of manual labor. For example, if you receive a spreadsheet where all names are in lowercase, you can use our Title Case function to properly capitalize the first letter of each name. If you have a block of text yelled in UPPERCASE, you can rapidly convert it to Sentence case to make it readable again.</p>

        <h3>Supported Text Transformations</h3>
        <p>Our <strong>change case tool</strong> supports several standard transformations, each serving a specific use case:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>UPPERCASE:</strong> Converts all letters to capitals. Useful for acronyms, legal disclaimers, or specific design aesthetics. E.g., "THIS IS UPPERCASE".</li>
          <li><strong>lowercase:</strong> Converts all letters to small cases. Often used by developers for standardizing database inputs, creating URL slugs, or matching variables. E.g., "this is lowercase".</li>
          <li><strong>Title Case:</strong> Capitalizes the first letter of every word. Also known as "Proper Case". This is essential for book titles, blog post headlines, names, and proper nouns. E.g., "This Is Title Case".</li>
          <li><strong>Sentence case:</strong> Capitalizes only the first letter of the first word in a sentence, and any word following a terminal punctuation mark (. ! ?). This is the standard format for regular paragraph text. E.g., "This is sentence case. It looks natural."</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Advanced Feature: Clean Whitespace</h3>
        <p>Beyond simple capitalization, our tool functions as a robust <strong>whitespace remover</strong>. Copying text from PDFs, legacy Word documents, or poorly formatted websites often introduces erratic spacing, double spaces, and random line breaks. By clicking the "Clean Whitespace" button, our algorithm strips out all duplicate spaces and normalizes line breaks, returning perfectly clean, single-spaced text.</p>

        <h3>Privacy and Security First</h3>
        <p>Data privacy is critical when handling potentially sensitive documents. Unlike other online converters that send your text to a server for processing, our <strong>client-side case converter</strong> executes all transformations entirely within your browser using JavaScript. Your text—whether it's a confidential email, proprietary code, or personal notes—never leaves your device. This guarantees 100% privacy and lightning-fast performance with zero latency.</p>
        
        <div class="faq-section" style="margin-top: 48px;">
          <h2 style="font-size: 24px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 24px;">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
          <details style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); padding: 16px 0; cursor: pointer;">
            <summary style="font-weight: 600; list-style: none; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center;">What is camelCase and when should I use it? <span style="opacity: 0.5;">+</span></summary>
            <p style="margin-top: 12px; font-size: 15px; color: var(--color-text-secondary); line-height: 1.6;">camelCase is a naming convention where the first letter of each word (except the first one) is capitalized, with no spaces between them (e.g., <code>myVariable</code>). It is the standard convention for variables and functions in JavaScript, Java, and C++.</p>
          </details>
          <details style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); padding: 16px 0; cursor: pointer;">
            <summary style="font-weight: 600; list-style: none; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center;">Is this case converter safe for sensitive documents? <span style="opacity: 0.5;">+</span></summary>
            <p style="margin-top: 12px; font-size: 15px; color: var(--color-text-secondary); line-height: 1.6;">Yes. All text processing occurs strictly client-side via JavaScript APIs. No HTTP requests are made, meaning your data never touches our servers. It is inherently safe for proprietary code, passwords, and PII.</p>
          </details>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>

    <aside class="ad-sidebar" aria-hidden="true">
      AdSense Unit | Responsive Vertical Skyscraper
    </aside>
  </div>

  <script>
    const input = document.getElementById('case-input');
    const output = document.getElementById('case-output');
    const statWords = document.getElementById('stat-words');
    const statChars = document.getElementById('stat-chars');
    const statParas = document.getElementById('stat-paras');

    function updateStats() {
      const text = input.value;
      const words = text.trim() === '' ? 0 : text.trim().split(/\s+/).length;
      const chars = text.length;
      const paras = text.trim() === '' ? 0 : text.split(/\n\s*\n/).filter(p => p.trim()).length || (text.trim() ? 1 : 0);
      statWords.textContent = words;
      statChars.textContent = chars;
      statParas.textContent = paras;
    }

    input.addEventListener('input', updateStats);

    function toTitleCase(str) {
      return str.replace(/\w\S*/g, (txt) =>
        txt.charAt(0).toUpperCase() + txt.substr(1).toLowerCase()
      );
    }

    function toSentenceCase(str) {
      return str.toLowerCase().replace(/(^|[.!?]\s+)(\w)/g, (match, p1, p2) =>
        p1 + p2.toUpperCase()
      );
    }

    function cleanWhitespace(str) {
      return str
        .split('\n')
        .map(line => line.replace(/\s+/g, ' ').trim())
        .filter((line, i, arr) => {
          if (line === '') {
            return i > 0 && arr[i - 1] !== '';
          }
          return true;
        })
        .join('\n')
        .trim();
    }

    document.getElementById('btn-upper').addEventListener('click', () => {
      output.value = input.value.toUpperCase();
    });
    document.getElementById('btn-lower').addEventListener('click', () => {
      output.value = input.value.toLowerCase();
    });
    document.getElementById('btn-title').addEventListener('click', () => {
      output.value = toTitleCase(input.value);
    });
    document.getElementById('btn-sentence').addEventListener('click', () => {
      output.value = toSentenceCase(input.value);
    });
    document.getElementById('btn-clean').addEventListener('click', () => {
      output.value = cleanWhitespace(input.value);
    });

    document.getElementById('btn-copy').addEventListener('click', async () => {
      const text = output.value;
      if (!text) {
        window.showToast?.('Nothing to copy');
        return;
      }
      try {
        await navigator.clipboard.writeText(text);
        window.showToast?.('Copied to clipboard!');
      } catch {
        // Fallback
        output.select();
        document.execCommand('copy');
        window.showToast?.('Copied to clipboard!');
      }
    });

    document.getElementById('btn-clear').addEventListener('click', () => {
      input.value = '';
      output.value = '';
      updateStats();
    });
  </script>
</MainLayout>
